<item>
            <title>[CXF-7815] Deal with java.security.acl classes being removed in Java 12</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7815</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8191138&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8191138&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The deprecated java.security.acl classes are being removed in 12. We should be prepared for that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13178002">CXF-7815</key>
            <summary>Deal with java.security.acl classes being removed in Java 12</summary>
