                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16669975" author="coheigea" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2018 11:29:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ffang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ffang&quot;&gt;ffang&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should add checks in DefaultSecurityContext and AbstractSecurityContextInInterceptor for java.security.acl.Group via reflection. Otherwise, login won&apos;t work with say an older version of Karaf that uses java.security.acl.Group instead. I wonder if we should also add a check for the Karaf Group interface again via reflection? If we don&apos;t then we are breaking backwards compatibility, as CXF + Karaf would work by default using java.security.acl.Group.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Colm.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16671076" author="ffang" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2018 03:41:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=coheigea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;coheigea&quot;&gt;coheigea&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good catch, on it!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Freeman&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16671192" author="ffang" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2018 07:25:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed by&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/commit/2566c8ff08e0b237d18c97bc919d32628eaa39ea&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cxf/commit/2566c8ff08e0b237d18c97bc919d32628eaa39ea&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16675049" author="coheigea" created="Mon, 5 Nov 2018 12:15:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Freeman! Just a minor improvement suggestion - we have multiple calls along the lines of:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;member instanceof GroupPrincipal&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; || instanceOf(member, &quot;java.security.acl.Group&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; || instanceOf(member, &quot;org.apache.karaf.jaas.boot.principal.Group&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead we could have a static method that encapsulates this &quot;isGroupPrincipal or something&quot; (and that also could be called from AbstractSecurityContextInInterceptor)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16678887" author="sean.mullan@oracle.com" created="Wed, 7 Nov 2018 22:30:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have deferred the removal of the java.security.acl APIs to JDK 13.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16679118" author="ffang" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2018 00:30:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sean.mullan%40oracle.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sean.mullan@oracle.com&quot;&gt;sean.mullan@oracle.com&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the info.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=coheigea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;coheigea&quot;&gt;coheigea&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yup, will revise accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16679182" author="ffang" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2018 02:04:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;revised here&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/commit/d89aa0baafba3d0433be054d45606e223479b620&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cxf/commit/d89aa0baafba3d0433be054d45606e223479b620&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
